      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IM THE FALCON NZ (11) returns to Jason Grimson after a stint in Queensland where he was runner-up two back at Albion Park. Owns a strong record at this distance and is talented enough to overcome the wide. Stablemate HUTA NZ (5) is likely improver. He has chased star mare Captains Mistress in his two starts so far this campaign, the latest at Listed level so will enjoy the class drop. He should be nearing peak fitness third-up. SOUTH SEAS ROCK NZ (6) made a good start for Seaton Grima when beaten 4m into third at this venue last week. Draws wider but is proven at this longer distance. MIKE ROSS NZ (1) has been close-up in two starts here since recording back-to-back wins. Owns a good record at this distance and draws to advantage as does HAVEYOUCHECKEDIN (3) who has finished runner-up in both starts this time in, missing by a nose last time. Returns to the city but races well third-up so could be peaking.",
